 country. Now we'd like you to visualise it - what can you do?</p><h2>Download the data</h2><p>• <a href=\"http://spreadsheets.google.com/ccc?key=t428ng6efkWu-fCkABi4YgQ\">DATA: download the full list, including descriptions of what the prize is for</a></p><h2>Can you do something with this data?</h2><p><strong>Flickr</strong> Please post your visualisations and mash-ups on our <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/groups/1115946@N24/\">Flickr group</a> or mail us at <a href=\"mailto:datastore@guardian.co.uk\">datastore@guardian.co.uk</a></p><p><strong>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/page/2009/jun/17/1\">Get the A-Z of data</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data-store\">More at the Datastore directory</a></strong><br /><strong>• <a href=\"http://twitter.com/datastore\">Follow us on Twitter</a></strong></p><h2>Data summary</h2><table>\n      <caption>\n            Nobel peace prize winners\n          </caption>\n      <thead>\n        <tr><th class=\"left\">Year</th><th class=\"left\">Winner, 1</th><th class=\"left\">Shared Winner, 2</th><th class=\"left\">Country, 1</th><th class=\"left\">Country, 2</th><th class=\"left\">Sex, 1</th><th class=\"left\">Sex, 2</th></tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td class=\"left\">1901 </td><td class=\"left\">Jean Henri Dunant </td><td class=\"left\">Frédéric Passy </td><td class=\"left\">Switz </td><td class=\"left\">Fra </td><td class=\"left\">M </td><td class=\"left\">M </td></tr><tr><td class=\"left\">1902 </td><td class=\"left\">Élie Ducommun </td><td class=\"left\">Charles Albert Gobat </td><td class=\"left\">Switz </td><td class=\"left\">Switz </td><td class=\"left\">M </td><td class=\"left\">M </td></tr><tr><td class=\"left\">1903 </td><td class=\"left\">Sir William Randal Cremer </td><td class=\"\"> </td><td class=\"left\">UK </td><td class=\"\"> </td><td class=\"left\">M </td><td class=\"\"> </td></tr><tr><td class=\"left\">1904 </td><td class=\"left\">Institute Of International Law 